"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-entertainment-2024-0726-1462090-lady-gaga-says-olympics-gig-was-supreme-honour\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"American singer Lady Gaga has said it was her \\\"supreme honour\\\" to perform at the Paris Olympics opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 113, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 8, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999997330733451, \"rank\": 1.8092365397308254e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 16, \"end\": 25, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lady Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 38-year-old surprised viewers by singing in French during her performance on Friday evening, which saw her deliver a burlesque take on the French classicMon Truc En Plume.\", \"from\": 115, \"to\": 290, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 163, \"end\": 169, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9042291617290236, \"rank\": 0.10209479031819582, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 258, \"end\": 264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9042291617290236, \"rank\": 0.10209479031819582, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Take a look at a gallery of the stars at the Paris Olympics opening ceremony here  On X, formerly Twitter, she said: \\\"I feel so completely grateful to have been asked to open the Paris @Olympics 2024 this year.\", \"from\": 292, \"to\": 502, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 390, \"end\": 397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.284583536184474e-20, \"text\": \"Twitter\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\"}, {\"begin\": 471, \"end\": 476, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.052955314289521e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am also humbled to be asked by the Olympics organising committee to sing such a special French song- a song to honour the French people and their tremendous history of art, music, and theatre.\", \"from\": 504, \"to\": 699, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 595, \"end\": 601, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9042291617290236, \"rank\": 0.10209479031819582, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 629, \"end\": 642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French people\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This song was sung by Zizi Jeanmaire, born in Paris a French ballerina, she famously sangMon Truc en Plumesin 1961.\", \"from\": 701, \"to\": 817, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 724, \"end\": 738, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zizi_Jeanmaire\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zizi Jeanmaire\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zizi_Jeanmaire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zizi_Jeanmaire\"}, {\"begin\": 748, \"end\": 753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.052955314289521e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The title means 'My Thing with Feathers'.\", \"from\": 819, \"to\": 861, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And this is not the first time we have crossed paths.\", \"from\": 862, \"to\": 915, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Zizi starred in Cole Porter's musicalAnything Goeswhich was my first jazz release.\\\"\", \"from\": 917, \"to\": 1001, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 918, \"end\": 922, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zizi_Strallen\", \"score\": 0.999999999965894, \"rank\": 2.2584049833936422e-11, \"text\": \"Zizi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zizi_Strallen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zizi_Strallen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I feel so completely grateful to have been asked to open the Paris@Olympics2024 this year.\", \"from\": 1003, \"to\": 1093, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am also humbled to be asked by the Olympics organizing committee to sing such a special French song-a song to honor the French people and their tremendous history of art, music, and\\u2026pic.twitter.com/FMNyiosHUR  She continued: \\\"Although I am not a French artist, I have always felt a very special connection with French people and singing French music.\", \"from\": 1094, \"to\": 1446, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1184, \"end\": 1190, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9042291617290236, \"rank\": 0.10209479031819582, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 1216, \"end\": 1229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French people\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 1342, \"end\": 1348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9042291617290236, \"rank\": 0.10209479031819582, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 1407, \"end\": 1420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French people\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 1433, \"end\": 1439, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9042291617290236, \"rank\": 0.10209479031819582, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I wanted nothing more than to create a performance that would warm the heart of France, celebrate French art and music, and on such a momentous occasion remind everyone of one of the most magical cities on earth - Paris.\", \"from\": 1448, \"to\": 1669, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1529, \"end\": 1535, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999999709578375, \"rank\": 1.4005144411633374e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1547, \"end\": 1553, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9042291617290236, \"rank\": 0.10209479031819582, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 1663, \"end\": 1668, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.052955314289521e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We rented pom poms from Le Lido archive - a real French cabaret theatre.\", \"from\": 1671, \"to\": 1744, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1721, \"end\": 1727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9042291617290236, \"rank\": 0.10209479031819582, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We collaborated with Dior to create custom costumes, using naturally moulted feathers.\", \"from\": 1746, \"to\": 1833, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I studied French choreography that put a modern twist on a French classic.\", \"from\": 1834, \"to\": 1908, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1844, \"end\": 1850, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9042291617290236, \"rank\": 0.10209479031819582, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 1893, \"end\": 1907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Classic_Races\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French classic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Classic_Races\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Classic_Races\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I rehearsed tirelessly to study a joyful French dance, brushing up on some old skills - I bet you did not know I used to dance at a 60s French party on the lower east side when I was first starting out.\", \"from\": 1910, \"to\": 2113, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1952, \"end\": 1958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9042291617290236, \"rank\": 0.10209479031819582, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 2047, \"end\": 2059, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French party\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Party\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I hope you love this performance as much as I do.\", \"from\": 2115, \"to\": 2165, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And to everyone in France, thank you so much for welcoming me to your country to sing in honour of you - it's a gift I will never forget.\\\"\", \"from\": 2166, \"to\": 2304, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2185, \"end\": 2191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999999709578375, \"rank\": 1.4005144411633374e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The singer congratulated the athletes who are competing and added that it was her \\\"supreme honour\\\" to sing for them.\", \"from\": 2306, \"to\": 2422, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On Friday evening, Lady Gaga emerged from a plume of pink feathers as she sang alongside a group of dancers while wearing a black bodice with a detachable black and pink ruffled skirt.\", \"from\": 2424, \"to\": 2608, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2443, \"end\": 2452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lady Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The singer, real name Stefani Germanotta, performed next to the River Seine, near the Notre Dame cathedral, during what is the first-ever opening ceremony to be staged outside a stadium.\", \"from\": 2610, \"to\": 2796, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2632, \"end\": 2650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stefani Germanotta\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}, {\"begin\": 2674, \"end\": 2685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the ceremony moved down the river, it paid tribute to the country's culture and history includingLes Miserables, a popular novel by Victor Hugo, which has subsequently been turned into a musical.\", \"from\": 2798, \"to\": 2996, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2933, \"end\": 2944, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Hugo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.50060177313002e-41, \"text\": \"Victor Hugo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Hugo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Hugo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Following a sequence paying homage to the historical epic, French heavy metal band Gojira performed at the Conciergerie, a former courthouse and prison in the city.\", \"from\": 2998, \"to\": 3162, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3057, \"end\": 3063, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9042291617290236, \"rank\": 0.10209479031819582, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 3081, \"end\": 3087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0452616610299615e-24, \"text\": \"Gojira\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\"}, {\"begin\": 3105, \"end\": 3117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conciergerie\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.27472711031577e-31, \"text\": \"Conciergerie\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conciergerie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conciergerie\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among the other performers was French-Malian singer Aya Nakamura, who sang while dressed in a golden dress paired with gladiator boots and gold jewellery.\", \"from\": 3164, \"to\": 3318, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3216, \"end\": 3228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aya Nakamura\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The celebrations were met with heavy rain with performers, including pianist Alexandre Kantorow, braving heavy showers during their performances.\", \"from\": 3320, \"to\": 3465, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3397, \"end\": 3415, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandre_Kantorow\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alexandre Kantorow\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandre_Kantorow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandre_Kantorow\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A total of 85 boats carried the team delegations on a four-mile journey through the centre of Paris, with more than 300,000 spectators lining the banks of the river.\", \"from\": 3467, \"to\": 3632, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3561, \"end\": 3566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.052955314289521e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Celebrities includingWickedstar Ariana Grande and and American singer Pharrell Williamsappeared at a red carpet event prior to the ceremony.\", \"from\": 3634, \"to\": 3774, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3688, \"end\": 3696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999997330733451, \"rank\": 1.8092365397308254e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Source: Press Association    \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026.\", \"from\": 3776, \"to\": 3816, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media.\", \"from\": 3817, \"to\": 3907, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3842, \"end\": 3865, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"score\": 0.9993664851270567, \"rank\": 0.0006339164685885233, \"text\": \"Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\"}, {\"begin\": 3867, \"end\": 3874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999867627595, \"rank\": 1.3237183061586725e-08, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": 